  "title": "AutoGPT request wrapper is vulnerable to DNS rebinding SSRF",
  "description": "AutoGPT's Requests wrapper validates a hostname before issuing a request, but then passes the hostname back to requests, which resolves it again. With a DNS rebinding hostname and TTL 0 records, the second resolution can return a blocked internal address, bypassing the intended SSRF boundary.",
